The paper deals with optimization problems related to scheduling and energy consumption, which are common topics in computer science. The use of speed-scaling mechanisms and the focus on non-preemptive scheduling suggest that the paper may belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) category. The use of approximation algorithms and the optimization of energy consumption suggest that the paper may also belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) categories. The consideration of parallel processors and the optimization of power functions suggest that the paper may belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) category. Finally, the use of mathematical models and the consideration of generalizations suggest that the paper may also belong to the cs.PF (Performance) category.
